HEADWORD: Grandfatherly
<hw>Grand"fa"ther*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Like a grandfather in age
or manner; kind; benignant; indulgent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was a <qex>grandfatherly</qex> sort of personage.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grandific</ent>⟦br⟧
